overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage and developing an an admin
  dashboard for data access. The approach involved updating the application's
  demographic data structure, defining a new  model in
  Prisma for a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB), and creating API endpoints for data
  submission, retrieval, and CSV export. A key decision was to implement a
  simple password-based authentication system for the admin dashboard, which was
  later refined to leverage Next.js middleware for more streamlined route
  protection. The implementation included building a login page and a dashboard
  to display responses. During testing, a minor issue was identified where the
  "Pre-fill & Jump to Report" feature did not trigger database saves, which was
  confirmed by directly testing the API.
